  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The advertisment display hereby approved shall be for a period of 5 years",
    "Condition : 2 - No advertisement shall be sited or displayed so as to-\r\n(a) endanger persons using any public highway, railway, waterway, dock, harbour or aerodrome (civil or military);\r\n(b) obscure, or hinder the ready interpretation of, any traffic sign, railway signal or aid to navigation by water or air; or\r\n(c) hinder the operation of any device used for the purpose of security or surveillance or for measuring the speed of any vehicle.",
    "Condition : 3 - Any advertisement displayed, and any site used for the display of advertisments, shall be maintained in a condition that does not impair the visual amenity of the site",
    "Condition : 4 - Where an advertisement is required under these Regulations to be removed, the site shall be left in a condition that does not endanger the public or impair visual amenity",
    "Condition : 5 - The proposed development shall be carried out in all respects in accordance with the proposals contained in the application and the plans submitted (Unnumbered site location plan, 9 page document showing [Specification sheet, Banner Specs, Bracket Specs; Bracket system for lamppost/ flag pole banners, Technical Drawing, How we install, lamppost elevation], Lamppost banner list spreadsheet, Lighting assessment, Photo example, received: 08/03/2021; Unnumbered block plan showing location of lampposts, received: 29/03/2021; CP Media Supporting Statement, received: 06/05/2021) therewith and approved by the Local Planning Authority, or as shall have been otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority before the building is used.",
    "Condition : 6 - The hereby approved advert banners shall be managed in strict accordance with the submitted CP Media Supporting Statement received 06/05/2021 and in accordance with said statement each new sponsor's artwork shall first be agreed in writing by the Council prior to installation.",
    "Condition : 7 - The hereby approved advert banners shall be installed at least 2.6 meters above the ground level of the footway immediately below."
  ],
